title: Queensland teen wrangles massive snake from beneath ute - 9news.com.au
text:
Queensland teen wrangles massive snake from beneath ute By Adam Duggan 
A Queensland teenager wrestled an enormous carpet python from beneath a ute before going to school on Wednesday morning. 
Wearing nothing but a pair of boardshorts and a heavy-duty glove on his right hand, Oli Wardrope, 14, wrestled the massive snake from the undercarriage of a ute. 
Yogi McDougall filmed the hair-raising snake wrangling , which has since been viewed more than 36,500 times on Facebook. 
The blonde teenager can be seen lying underneath the Toyota Cruiser as the snake slithers across his face and chest. 
"Do you think he'd squeeze through all that mate?" one onlooker asks. 
"Yeah, I won't be able to get him by the head because I have to pull him out by the head and it won't work," Oli responds. 
With his gloved hand, he grabs the snake's head and holds its mouth shut. 
"I've got his head, I've got his head, I've got his head," Oli gleefully says. 
As he slides out from beneath the car, the full size of the carpet python becomes apparent. 
"F---ing hell lad. That's a big snake," A shocked onlooker says. 
Another man helps Oli put the snake into a bag. 
Oli's father, Chazza Wardrope, gives his son a congratulatory handshake and expresses his pride. 
"That's my boy. Been wrangling snakes since he was five." Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
